org.activebpel.rt.bpel.impl
Interface IAeBusinessProcessEngineInternal

All Superinterfaces:
IAeBusinessProcessEngine, IAeBusinessProcessFactory
All Known Subinterfaces:
IAeRecoveryEngine
All Known Implementing Classes:
AeBusinessProcessEngine, AeRecoveryEngine
public interface IAeBusinessProcessEngineInternal
extends IAeBusinessProcessEngine, IAeBusinessProcessFactory

Internal extensions to business process engine allows classes within the implemenation to use the engine while still hiding the implementor.

removeAlarm

public boolean removeAlarm(long aProcessId,
                           int aLocationPathId,
                           int aAlarmId)
                    throws AeBusinessProcessException
Removes an alarm. The removal of an alarm requires it to be unscheduled (cancelled) in addition to whatever other bookkeeping must be done by the alarm manager implementation. Note that removeAlarm will be called by the engine when an alarm should be cancelled (not fired) as well as when the alarm was fired and must now be removed from whatever internal storage the alarm manager implementation is using.

Parameters:
aProcessId - The ID of the BPEL process this alarm is associated with.
aLocationPathId - The location path id of the alarm receiver.
aAlarmId - alarm id
Returns:
True if the alarm was successfully removed.
Throws:
AeBusinessProcessException

queueReceiveData

public IAeWebServiceResponse queueReceiveData(IAeProcessPlan aPlan,
                                              IAeMessageContext aContext,
                                              IAeMessageData aData)
                                       throws AeBusinessProcessException,
                                              AeTimeoutException
Specialized version of queue receive data that accepts the process plan. This method is intended to be used by our internal web service layer to route messages to the engine. In that layer, we need to load the deployment plan for the process in order to deserialize the SOAP message into our message data container.

Parameters:
aPlan - Process plan for routing the message
aContext - provides contextual information for message like partner link being targeted
aData - contains the data extracted from the inbound message
Throws:
AeBusinessProcessException
AeTimeoutException

queueReceiveData

public long queueReceiveData(IAeMessageData aMessageData,
                             IAeReplyReceiver aReply,
                             IAeMessageContext aContext,
                             IAeMessageAcknowledgeCallback aAckCallback,
                             boolean aQueueForExecution)
                      throws AeCorrelationViolationException,
                             AeConflictingRequestException,
                             AeBusinessProcessException
Accepts an inbound message which will either create a new process instance or get dispatched to an existing message receiver from an already executing process. If a new process was created, then this method returns the newly created process id otherwise, returns IAeBusinessProcess.NULL_PROCESS_ID. If the aQueueForExecution was false, then the newly created process is not queued for execution.

Parameters:
aMessageData - message data
aReply - message reply receiver
aContext - message context
aAckCallback - durable messaging callback
aQueueForExecution - if true and a process was created, it will be queued for execution.
Returns:
If a process was created, then the process id is returned, else returns IAeBusinessProcess.NULL_PROCESS_ID.
Throws:
AeCorrelationViolationException
AeConflictingRequestException
AeBusinessProcessException
